{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VH4jv1ocT6XB7F6F4JkU7o","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * step1.cu -- K_Step1 SPH density summation + strain-rate tensor + heat diffusion kernel.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Per-particle computation:\n     5→ *   density_sum += m_j * (h^2 - |r_ij|^2)^3   for all neighbors j within h\n     6→ *   density_i = max(1.0, poly6_coeff * density_sum)\n     7→ *\n     8→ * Heat diffusion (all particles):\n     9→ *   dTdt += kappa_i * viscosity_lap_coeff * sum_j (m_j/rho_j) * (T_j - T_i) * (h - |r_ij|)\n    10→ *   where kappa_i = c_materials[mat_id].thermal_conductivity\n    11→ *\n    12→ * For GRANULAR particles only, also computes the symmetric strain-rate tensor D\n    13→ * using the SPH velocity gradient with spiky gradient weighting:\n    14→ *   D_ab = 0.5 * sum_j (m_j/rho_j) * (dv_a * gradW_b + dv_b * gradW_a)\n    15→ * Then: gamma_dot = sqrt(2 * D:D) = sqrt(2 * (Dxx^2 + Dyy^2 + Dzz^2 + 2*(Dxy^2 + Dxz^2 + Dyz^2)))\n    16→ *\n    17→ * Operates on SORTED particle arrays (after hash + sort + reorder).\n    18→ * Uses 27-cell neighbor iteration with grid cell_start/cell_end tables.\n    19→ * Self-interaction IS included for density (j==i NOT skipped).\n    20→ * Self-interaction is skipped for strain-rate and heat diffusion (j==i skipped).\n    21→ * Per-particle mass m_j supports multi-material and mass splitting.\n    22→ *\n    23→ * Ported from SPHSimLib/K_SimpleSPH_Step1.inl + K_SPH_Kernels_poly6.inl.\n    24→ * Neighbor iteration ported from SPHSimLib/K_UniformGrid_Utils.inl.\n    25→ *\n    26→ * Constant memory (c_grid, c_sim, c_precalc, c_materials) declared in common.cuh.\n    27→ */\n    28→\n    29→#include \"common.cuh\"\n    30→\n    31→extern \"C\" __global__\n    32→void K_Step1(\n    33→    uint            numParticles,\n    34→    const float4*   __restrict__ position,      // sorted positions\n    35→    const float4*   __restrict__ velocity,      // sorted velocities (for strain-rate)\n    36→    const float*    __restrict__ mass,           // sorted per-particle mass\n    37→    const float*    __restrict__ density_in,     // sorted density from previous step (for strain-rate m_j/rho_j weighting; NULL on first frame)\n    38→    const uint*     __restrict__ packed_info,    // sorted packed_info (for behavior class check)\n    39→    const float*    __restrict__ temperature_in, // sorted temperature (for heat diffusion)\n    40→    const uint*     __restrict__ cell_start,     // grid cell start indices\n    41→    const uint*     __restrict__ cell_end,       // grid cell end indices\n    42→    float*          __restrict__ density_out,    // output: density per particle\n    43→    float*          __restrict__ shear_rate_out, // output: gamma_dot per particle (0 for non-GRANULAR)\n    44→    float*          __restrict__ dTdt_out        // output: temperature rate of change (heat diffusion)\n    45→) {\n    46→    uint index_i = blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;\n    47→    if (index_i >= numParticles) return;\n    48→\n    49→    // Read position of particle i\n    50→    float4 pos4_i = position[index_i];\n    51→    float3 pos_i = make_float3(pos4_i.x, pos4_i.y, pos4_i.z);\n    52→\n    53→    float h    = c_sim.smoothing_length;\n    54→    float h_sq = c_sim.smoothing_length_sq;\n    55→\n    56→    // Check if this particle is GRANULAR\n    57→    uint pi_i = __ldg(&packed_info[index_i]);\n    58→    int behavior_i = GET_BEHAVIOR(pi_i);\n    59→    uint mat_id_i = GET_MATERIAL_ID(pi_i);\n    60→    bool is_granular = (behavior_i == GRANULAR);\n    61→\n    62→    // Read velocity for strain-rate (only used if GRANULAR, but cheap to read)\n    63→    float3 vel_i;\n    64→    if (is_granular) {\n    65→        float4 vel4_i = velocity[index_i];\n    66→        vel_i = make_float3(vel4_i.x, vel4_i.y, vel4_i.z);\n    67→    }\n    68→\n    69→    // Read temperature for heat diffusion\n    70→    float T_i = __ld