{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016fbVK7ZDtEAyBGBk2RTpNg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nUS-021 is complete. Here's what was implemented:\n\n**Step1 CUDA kernel (`step1.cu`):**\n- Added `exposure_heat_out` and `exposure_corrode_out` kernel output parameters\n- In the neighbor loop (self-interaction skipped), accumulates exposure via pure `c_interactions[mat_i][mat_j]` table lookup -- no branching on material type\n- `exposure_corrode += reaction_rate * W_poly6(r_sq, h_sq)`\n- `exposure_heat += heat_exchange * max(T_j - T_i, 0) * W_poly6(r_sq, h_sq)`\n- PostCalc applies `poly6_coeff` normalization to both accumulators\n\n**Python wrapper (`step1.py`):**\n- Added `upload_interactions()` for `c_interactions` constant memory\n- `compute_step1()` now returns 5-tuple: `(density, shear_rate, dTdt, exposure_heat, exposure_corrode)`\n\n**Pipeline (`simulation.py`, `world.py`):**\n- `sorted_exposure_heat` and `sorted_exposure_corrode` buffers pre-allocated in World\n- `c_interactions` uploaded to step1 module at init\n- Exposure buffers wired through the step1 call\n\n**Tests (all 20 pass):**\n- Acid near metal → metal's `exposure_corrode > 0` (5534)\n- Fire near wood → wood's `exposure_heat > 0` (33.5M), fire's = 0\n- Water near water → both exposures == 0\n- 500K stress test validates all exposure values are finite and non-negative\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":463,"cache_read_input_tokens":131326,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":463},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40989a4b-7ef9-4e02-8a7d-030d3ce20abf","uuid":"f89a80a9-b5c9-40d7-a4c7-acad342e6d0d"}
